kernel_variant.question:
For a fixed positive integer m define  
  F_m(x)= (x^{2m}+1)(x^{2m}+9) \in  \mathbb{R}[x].

Let N(m) be the number of ordered pairs of real-coefficient polynomials  

  (A(x), B(x)) \in  \mathbb{R}[x]^2  

that satisfy simultaneously  

(1) A(x)^2 + B(x)^2 = F_m(x);  
(2) deg A > deg B;  
(3) A(x) is monic;  
(4) B(0)=0;  
(5) gcd(A,B)=1.

Determine a closed arithmetic formula for N(m) in terms of m.  
(The use of complex numbers and of the orthogonality relations for m-th roots of unity is allowed.)

